‘We can’t say we are grateful because we would rather him not have done 
that at all. It is an awful thing at any time — not just this particular
week. It is nice to know he knows he has let himself, the club, the 
fans and the (Hillsborough) families down.

‘We could refuse to accept it but it is going to have to go to someone, 
and he wants to show respect and remorse to the families.’

Suarez has been genuinely  contrite following the latest  disgraceful 
episode of his career and the PFA, who said it would be ‘embarrassing’ 
if he were named Player of the Year next Sunday, have offered to help 
with improving his behaviour.

He will receive the same help at Anfield. Liverpool employ top 
psychologist Dr Steve Peters, who is credited with playing an 
instrumental role in transforming the fortunes of British cycling.

