‘Luis issued his apology and then we spoke with him last night and then 
again this morning. We’ve taken action to fine Luis for his actions.’ 

Liverpool, however, have received criticism for not issuing their own 
suspension and for leaving it to the FA to deal with the incident.

Yet some Liverpool fans will believe that for Suarez to face such a big 
ban is unjust, given what happened to Tottenham’s Jermain Defoe in 2006 
when he bit Javier Mascherano. Since that incident, though, the FA have 
completely changed their rule book and had that incident occurred now, 
Defoe — who was booked during that game against West Ham — would have 
been charged again, given the exceptional circumstances.

There has been no hiding place for Suarez in the last 24 hours and his 
personal sponsors, adidas, issued a strongly worded statement to condemn
an incident that has left the game stunned.

